captionText: The world is a book and those who do not travel read only one page.
author: Saint Augustine

captionText: Travel is the only thing you buy that makes you richer.
author: Unknown

captionText: Adventure awaits.
author: Unknown

captionText: Wander often, wonder always.
author: Unknown

captionText: Life is short and the world is wide.
author: Unknown

captionText: Travel far enough, you meet yourself.
author: David Mitchell

captionText: Jobs fill your pocket, but adventures fill your soul.
author: Unknown

captionText: The journey of a thousand miles begins with a single step.
author: Lao Tzu

captionText: Not all who wander are lost.
author: J.R.R. Tolkien

captionText: Traveling – it leaves you speechless, then turns you into a storyteller.
author: Ibn Battuta

captionText: Adventure is worthwhile.
author: Aesop

captionText: Travel is fatal to prejudice, bigotry, and narrow-mindedness.
author: Mark Twain

captionText: The gladdest moment in human life is a departure into unknown lands.
author: Sir Richard Burton

captionText: To travel is to live.
author: Hans Christian Andersen

captionText: Travel makes one modest. You see what a tiny place you occupy in the world.
author: Gustave Flaubert

captionText: We wander for distraction, but we travel for fulfillment.
author: Hilaire Belloc

captionText: Travel and change of place impart new vigor to the mind.
author: Seneca

captionText: Travel is never a matter of money but of courage.
author: Paulo Coelho

captionText: Traveling tends to magnify all human emotions.
author: Peter Hoeg

captionText: Live life with no excuses, travel with no regret.
author: Oscar Wilde

captionText: The world is yours to explore.
